race.comment: SOUTHERN DANCER (6) was doing his best work late when finishing full of running at Cootamundra when resuming over a shorter trip. Steps up in journey and should prove very tough to stop with McDougall piloting from the gun draw. MAID IN DUBAI (3) also wound up strongly at Cootamundra last time out, finishing half a length away in third, in a much-improved performance. Easier this time and brings the right form. TAUMATA (5) returns and it's worth noting he filled a minor placing when first-up here on the main track over 1400m. Will be looking for further later but this a good kickoff point for him. Watch for him late. SWEET TREATS (7) came desperately close to making it two on the bounce last start. Doesn't have to improve much to be in the finish again. Expect her to be in this for a long way.
